agent-worker - Agent Task Worker

USAGE:
    agent-worker <agent-job> [options...]

DESCRIPTION:
    Execute a specific agent task. Can run locally or remotely.
    Initializes git workspace and runs the specified job.

ARGUMENTS:
    agent-job
        Path to agent task file (required)

    options...
        Additional options passed to the job

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-agent-remote-host HOST
        Remote host for execution

    -conf-agent-remote-user USER
        Remote user for execution

EXAMPLES:
    agent-worker /path/to/job.sh
    agent-worker task.sh --option=value
